startSearch

private boolean startSearch(DMItem node,
                            java.lang.String clause)
Run a search on each of the node's children. We start with this function instead of searchNode to deal with that special case where the use has chosen to search top-state. As we descend, we don't want to continually search through top-state, because that will never end. searchNode ignores the top-state.

Parameters:
node - The node to begin the search on.
clause - The node name to look for.
Returns:
true if we found a match, false if not.

searchNode

private boolean searchNode(DMItem node,
                           java.lang.String clause)
Recurses through this node and its children to find a match. Ignores the top-state's children to avoid infinite recursion.

Parameters:
node - The node to search.
clause - The node name to look for.
Returns:
true if we found a match, false if not.
